Hello Lenny,

Thank you for contacting Netwrix Technical Support. 

To help us streamline the troubleshooting process and resolve your issue more efficiently, please provide the following information:  

What is the impact of the issue on your business? 
Who is affected by this issue? 
What steps to troubleshoot the issue have already been taken? 
What are you trying to do or accomplish? 
Is this a new configuration, data collection or report? 
If no, has anything changed in your environment since the last time it worked? 
When did this issue start?  
What are the steps to reproduce? 
What software is currently installed - run this command from an admin Powershell prompt:
Get-CimInstance -Class Win32_Product |Where-Object {($_.Name -Like "Stealth*" -or $_.Name -like "Netwrix*" -or $_.Name -like "Postg*" -or ` $_.Name -like "Python*")} -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue

Please perform the follow steps and upload the resulting Artifacts:

Enable Debug Logging
From the NEA Console > Settings > Application
Set Log Level to Debug
Rerun jobs that are failing to collect logs in full detail. Return Log level to warning afterwards.


Please provide logs from the following locations: 
Enterprise Auditor Console: %SAInstallDir%SADatabaseLogsApplication 
Access Information Center (11.6): C:Program FilesSTEALTHbitsAccess Information Center 
Access Information (11.5): C:inetpubwwwrootStealthAUDIT Compliance 

Export of Job(s) – note jobs may be nested under multiple Groups:
Right click on the Job or Job Group experiencing problems and select Export. This creates .zip file containing all logs and configuration settings of your jobs that we can import and review.


From the Job Status Export the Messages Table, CSV is preferred: 
 

Thank you,

Technical Support Engineer

TextBody: Hi {{{Recipient.FirstName}}}, Thank you for the updated information. I will close the ticket. Below is a brief summary. Hello Lenny, I am glad that we were able to get your issue resolved. The following is a summary of the ticket for your records. Symptom A bunch of accounts with passwords not expiring are missing from this report. The SQL Query for the job is below. DROP TABLE [StealthAudit].[dbo].[SA_RS_PassNeverExpires] SELECT [uv].[PrincipalId] AS [PrincipalId] ,ISNULL([uv].[DisplayName],[uv].[NTAccount]) AS [User] ,[uv].[DistinguishedName] AS [Distinguished Name] ,[epv].[canonicalName] as [Canoncial Name] ,[uv].[Title] AS [Title] ,[epv].[physicaldeliveryofficename] AS [Office] ,[uv].[NTAccount] AS [NT Account] ,[uv].[Description] AS [Decription] ,[uv].IsDeleted ,[epv].[Info] AS [Notes] ,[uv].Mail ,uv.[PwdLastSetDate] as [Last Set] ,[epv].[extensionAttribute4] as [Owner] ,CAST([uv].[LastLogonTimestamp] AS date) AS [Last Logon] ,CAST([uv].[WhenCreated] AS date) AS [Created On] ,DATEDIFF(dd,[uv].[lastLogonTimeStamp],GETUTCDATE()) AS [Days since last Logon] ,CASE WHEN [uv].[AccountExpires] < GETDATE() THEN 'True' ELSE 'False' END AS [Account Expired] ,CASE WHEN [uv].[ACCOUNTDISABLE] = 0 then 'False' ELSE 'True' END AS [Disabled], DATEDIFF(dd, UV.PwdLastSetDate, GETUTCDATE()) AS [Password Age], CASE WHEN UV.PASSWD_NOTREQD = 1 THEN 'True' ELSE 'False' END AS [Not Required], CASE WHEN UV.PASSWD_CANT_CHANGE = 1 THEN 'True' ELSE 'False' End AS [Can't Change], CASE WHEN UV.DONT_EXPIRE_PASSWORD = 1 THEN 'True' ELSE 'False' End AS [Never Expire] INTO [StealthAudit].[dbo].[SA_RS_PassNeverExpires] FROM [StealthAudit].[dbo].[SA_ADInventory_UsersView] as [uv] inner join [StealthAudit].[dbo].[SA_ADInventory_ExtendedAttributesPivotView] as [epv] on [uv].PrincipalID = [epv].PrincipalID where [uv].IsDeleted = 0 and [uv].SamAccountName not like '%healthmailbox%' and [uv].DONT_EXPIRE_PASSWORD = 1 and [uv].Mail not like '%company.com%' and [uv].Mail not like '%departed%' and [uv].DomainId = 1 Cause Issues with a table referenced in the custom report. Resolution DB team identified an issue with a problematic table. Following this email, you will receive an automated confirmation that the case is closed, along with the ability to re-open the case if any related errors return. In addition, you will also receive a separate email with a survey where you can let us know how we did. Feel free to leave any feedback via the survey link! Thank you, Scottie Taylor Technical Support Engineer ____________________________ Cybersecurity That Works For You 6160 Warren Parkway, Suite 100, Frisco, TX 75034 www.netwrix.com --------------- Original Message --------------- From: Jones, Lenny T.
